    <h2>"Gollash" With Meat</h2>
    <br />
    <a href="egyptianDishes.aspx">Back</a>
    <br />
    <br />
    Name: &quot;Gollash&quot; with meat<br />
    Submitted by: Ibrahim<br />
    Prepare Time: 00:45:00<br />
    <br />
    INGREDIENTS:
    <br /><br />
1 package Athens® Fillo Dough (9″ x 14″), thawed
<br />
1/3 cup + 2 tablespoons olive oil
<br />
3/4 cup sweet onion, thinly sliced 
<br />
1 1/4 pounds beef
<br />
1 tablespoon garlic, minced 
<br />
1/2 teaspoon + 1 pinch salt
<br />
1/4 teaspoon + 1 pinch pepper
<br />
1/2 teaspoon allspice
<br />
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
<br />
1/3 cup butter, melted 
<br />
1 egg + 1 egg yolk 
<br />
1 cup milk 
<br /><br />
How To Cook It:
<br /><br />
1.Thaw two rolls of fillo, following thawing instructions on package. Preheat oven to 350⁰F.
<br />
2.Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large frying pan.
<br /> 
3.Add onions and cook covered for 5-10 minutes or until onions become soft and begin to brown. 
<br />
4.Add beef, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, allspice and cinnamon. 
<br />
5.Cook over medium heat until meat has browned.
<br />
6.Remove from heat and set aside.
<br />
7.Whisk together 1/3 cup each olive oil and butter.
<br />
8.Lightly brush a 9” x 13” baking pan. 
<br />
9.Unroll and cover fillo sheets with plastic wrap, then a slightly damp towel to prevent drying out. 
<br />
10.Lay three sheets of fillo in the baking pan. 
<br />
11.Liberally brush top sheet with oil/butter mixture. 
<br />
12.Repeat this process until one roll of dough is used, tucking in any excess dough.
<br />
13.Spread meat mixture on top of dough. 
<br />
14.Layer the second roll of dough on top in the same way until the second roll is used. 
<br />
15.Brush the top layer thoroughly with oil/butter mixture. 
<br />
16.Cut the pie into 12 equal pieces. Whisk egg and egg yolk into milk. 
<br />
17.Add a pinch each of salt and pepper. 
<br />
18.Pour this mixture evenly over top of pie. 
<br />
19.Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown
